text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus rupestris is the accepted name of an endemic small tree species in the Asian sub-genus of 'ring-cupped oaks' and the family Fagaceae.This is a small tree species, growing to 5–6 m, which appears to be endemic to Vietnam, where it may be called sồi vùng đá  There are no known sub-species.
